	•	app/integrations/telegram/
	•	app/integrations/llm/
	•	app/utils/timezone.py
	•	app/db/models/
	•	app/db/repositories/

Target frontend module map:
	•	src/api/
	•	src/features/
	•	src/pages/
	•	src/components/
	•	src/hooks/
	•	src/utils/

⸻

15. How Cursor should work with this architecture

For any medium or large task:
	1.	identify affected architecture layer
	2.	list files to change
	3.	explain why
	4.	implement smallest safe step
	5.	describe manual test scenario

Cursor must not perform uncontrolled cross-layer rewrites.

⸻

16. Success criteria for the architecture

The architecture is considered successful when:
	•	Telegram and Web share core logic
	•	dialog state is stable and centralized
	•	intent logic is centralized
	•	booking logic is service-based
	•	time is consistent everywhere
	•	frontend is production-safe
	•	LLM is optional and bounded
	•	new features can be added without breaking booking flow
